{"article_id":"6pV69Z14no8PTcAL","edus":[{"id":0,"text":"While President Trump took a victory lap with House Republicans","depth":5},{"id":1,"text":"after their health care bill passed its first big test Thursday ,","depth":5},{"id":2,"text":"the hard work is just beginning for the majority party","depth":5},{"id":3,"text":"whose mission these past seven years has been ObamaCare ' s demise .","depth":5},{"id":4,"text":"Senate approval will be a much higher bar","depth":6},{"id":5,"text":"to clear :","depth":6},{"id":6,"text":"There ' s no shortage of bipartisan criticism from the upper chamber right now ,","depth":6},{"id":7,"text":"and the GOP holds a considerably smaller majority margin on that half of the Hill .","depth":6},{"id":8,"text":"All this means Republican senators almost certainly will rewrite the legislation ,","depth":7},{"id":9,"text":"or start over ,","depth":7},{"id":10,"text":"as the deliberative body takes up the issue - at its own pace .","depth":6},{"id":11,"text":"Sen. Bill Cassidy , R-La. , said","depth":8},{"id":12,"text":"the Senate will write its own bill ,","depth":8},{"id":13,"text":"stressing","depth":8},{"id":14,"text":"senators still need to see an official estimate on the updated plan ' s impact for consumers and taxpayers","depth":9},{"id":15,"text":"- something","depth":10},{"id":16,"text":"the House did not have in hand","depth":11},{"id":17,"text":"when Republicans narrowly approved the American Health Care Act on a 217-213 vote Thursday .","depth":11},{"id":18,"text":"`` We must manage expectations","depth":8},{"id":19,"text":"and remain focused on the art of the doable","depth":9},{"id":20,"text":"as we move forward , ''","depth":9},{"id":21,"text":"Senate Finance Committee Chairman Orrin Hatch , R-Utah , said in a statement .","depth":7},{"id":22,"text":"Republicans enjoy a relatively comfortable margin in the House .","depth":6},{"id":23,"text":"Even with that , an earlier version of the bill had to be yanked from the floor in March for lack of support ;","depth":7},{"id":24,"text":"and with 20 GOP defections on Thursday , the majority party was just two votes shy of another collapse .","depth":7},{"id":25,"text":"The Senate is different , and arguably trickier .","depth":6},{"id":26,"text":"Republicans have a slim 52-48 majority ,","depth":9},{"id":27,"text":"and it takes 60 votes","depth":10},{"id":28,"text":"to pass most legislation .","depth":10},{"id":29,"text":"Republicans are eyeing special rules","depth":10},{"id":30,"text":"to pass a version with a simple majority","depth":11},{"id":31,"text":"( or 50 votes plus a tie-breaker from Vice President Pence ) .","depth":11},{"id":32,"text":"But not only do those rules limit what changes can be considered ,","depth":10},{"id":33,"text":"it ' s far from a sure thing that Majority Leader Mitch McConnell , R-Ky. , can cobble together 50 or 51 votes .","depth":10},{"id":34,"text":"And","depth":8},{"id":35,"text":"if a different version does pass the Senate ,","depth":9},{"id":36,"text":"that would have to be reconciled with the House bill .","depth":9},{"id":37,"text":"McConnell indicated in a statement","depth":6},{"id":38,"text":"the Senate plans to act , in some capacity .","depth":6},{"id":39,"text":"\" Obamacare has failed the American people","depth":8},{"id":40,"text":"and must be repealed and replaced , \"","depth":8},{"id":41,"text":"he said .","depth":7},{"id":42,"text":"\" As Congress considers this legislation ,","depth":7},{"id":43,"text":"the administration will continue working","depth":9},{"id":44,"text":"to deliver relief","depth":10},{"id":45,"text":"and stabilize health markets ,","depth":10},{"id":46,"text":"and Congress will continue to act on legislation","depth":9},{"id":47,"text":"to provide more choices and freedom in health care decisions . \"","depth":9},{"id":48,"text":"The House bill","depth":10},{"id":49,"text":"as passed","depth":10},{"id":50,"text":"would scrap the Affordable Care Act ' s penalties","depth":10},{"id":51,"text":"for not buying insurance","depth":10},{"id":52,"text":"as well as a number of taxes ;","depth":8},{"id":53,"text":"replace subsidies for insurance with tax credits ;","depth":8},{"id":54,"text":"cut Medicaid ;","depth":9},{"id":55,"text":"and pull back on coverage requirements for insurance companies .","depth":9},{"id":56,"text":"In a provision","depth":8},{"id":57,"text":"that helped the bill pass the House ,","depth":8},{"id":58,"text":"the new version would let states get a waiver","depth":8},{"id":59,"text":"so insurers can set higher premiums for those with pre-existing conditions .","depth":8},{"id":60,"text":"Republican supporters of the bill say","depth":7},{"id":61,"text":"changes are necessary","depth":8},{"id":62,"text":"to curb rising premiums","depth":9},{"id":63,"text":"and prevent insurers from fleeing markets across the country .","depth":9},{"id":64,"text":"But critics say","depth":7},{"id":65,"text":"the changes would make the system worse","depth":8},{"id":66,"text":"- leading to higher costs for the most vulnerable patients .","depth":8},{"id":67,"text":"Rarely one for understatement , Sen. Elizabeth Warren , D-Mass. , tweeted ,","depth":6},{"id":68,"text":"\" # AHCA will devastate Americans ' healthcare .","depth":7},{"id":69,"text":"Families will go bankrupt .","depth":8},{"id":70,"text":"People will die . \"","depth":8},{"id":71,"text":"But moderate Republicans have plenty of concerns about the language , too .","depth":8},{"id":72,"text":"Sen. Lindsey Graham , R-S.C. , went on a tweet-storm","depth":10},{"id":73,"text":"blasting ObamaCare in its current form","depth":11},{"id":74,"text":"while calling for a bipartisan replacement .","depth":11},{"id":75,"text":"He warned","depth":10},{"id":76,"text":"the House version \" has not been scored ,","depth":11},{"id":77,"text":"amendments not allowed ,","depth":13},{"id":78,"text":"and 3 hours final debate","depth":13},{"id":79,"text":"-- should be viewed with caution . \"","depth":12},{"id":80,"text":"Moderates are worried about the Medicaid cuts and other provisions .","depth":8},{"id":81,"text":"Sen . Rob Portman , R-Ohio , said","depth":9},{"id":82,"text":"he does not support the bill","depth":11},{"id":83,"text":"\" as currently constructed \"","depth":11},{"id":84,"text":"for that reason .","depth":10},{"id":85,"text":"Meanwhile , conservative senators bring their own set of possible changes .","depth":7},{"id":86,"text":"Sen. Ted Cruz , R-Texas , said","depth":9},{"id":87,"text":"lawmakers \" should continue to improve the bill \"","depth":9},{"id":88,"text":"Sen. Rand Paul , R-Ky. , told Fox News ' Neil Cavuto","depth":10},{"id":89,"text":"that House conservatives \" made the bill a lot less bad \"","depth":11},{"id":90,"text":"but he ' s still concerned about payments to insurance companies .","depth":11},{"id":91,"text":"\" It ' s going to take a little bit of work to get me to a yes vote ,","depth":11},{"id":92,"text":"but I do have an open mind , \"","depth":11},{"id":93,"text":"he said .","depth":10},{"id":94,"text":"Trump on Friday stayed positive about the bill ' s chances","depth":3},{"id":95,"text":"-","depth":4},{"id":96,"text":"after having successfully helped revive the plan , with Speaker Paul Ryan , in the House .","depth":4},{"id":97,"text":"\" Big win in the House","depth":5},{"id":98,"text":"-","depth":6},{"id":99,"text":"very exciting !","depth":6},{"id":100,"text":"But","depth":5},{"id":101,"text":"when everything comes together with the inclusion of Phase 2 ,","depth":6},{"id":102,"text":"we will have truly great healthcare ! \"","depth":6},{"id":103,"text":"he tweeted .","depth":3}],"relations":[{"parent":207,"left":197,"right":206,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":197,"left":125,"right":196,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":125,"left":107,"right":124,"relation":"adversative","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":107,"left":105,"right":106,"relation":"context","nuclearity":"SN"},{"pa